Authorities say all bodies have gunshot wounds on the upper body and the motive for the killings is still unknown. JOHANNESBURG Gauteng police say they are investigating cases of murder after six bodies were found in an open veld next to a railway line in Benoni in the East Rand.It s understood a passer-by called the police after he came across the bodies in the early hours of today.Authorities say all bodies have gunshot wounds on the upper body and the motive for the killings is still unknown.Police spokesperson Mavela Masondo says the bodies are not yet identified. It s suspected that the deceased were murdered elsewhere and then taken to where they were found. It s also suspected that they were illegal miners. 